		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have had problem trying to capture from NES. It seemed like the device that I used only supported 25/30 fps. 
<br />
<br />The result was that for instance recording from Super Mario Bros. and being "big mario" and when I got small after tocuhing an enemy... Mario starts to blink fast. The device only recorded the frames when mario wasn't visible. Meaning it looks like he got invicible for the short time when he was blinking:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=heHlDHbf5aY">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=heHlDHbf5aY</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />edit: Youtube screwed up the audio. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />
